K", "INCI.JK", "SEMA.JK", "TNCA.JK", "GTSI.JK", "PEVE.JK", "TRIL.JK", "PNSE.JK", "IOTF.JK", "MRAT.JK", "ARKA.JK", "CHIP.JK", "YELO.JK", "PORT.JK", "MAGP.JK", "HADE.JK", "IBOS.JK", "TIRA.JK", "PSDN.JK", "MAPB.JK", "ASJT.JK", "BIPP.JK", "CTBN.JK", "SONA.JK", "VKTR.JK", "BSML.JK", "RELF.JK", "LMPI.JK", "KBAG.JK", "DEPO.JK", "IPPE.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-09-18T17:19:28", "title": "Astra International to Launch 3 New Battery EV Models in 2 Years to Compete with Chinese Manufacturers in Indonesia's Growing EV Market"}, {"body": "PT Kaltim Prima Coal, a subsidiary of PT Bumi Resources, is planning to partner on a coal downstream project, with an initial investment value of $322.26 million, and is expected to announce the plan by the end of the year. In its financial report for the first semester of 2024, Bumi's revenue decreased to $2.59 billion, operating profit fell to $12.31 million, but net profit rose to $84.91 million, driven by increased gold sales and steady coal exports.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/50940/kpc-downstream-coal-sector", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Energy Commodities", "Metals and Minerals", "Gold", "Earnings Report", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-09-18T15:41:49", "title": "PT Kaltim Prima Coal, a subsidiary of PT Bumi Resources, is seeking partners for a coal downstream project."}, {"body": "Anindya Novyan Bakrie, newly appointed General Chairperson of the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry, holds key positions in several companies, including PT Visi Media Asia Tbk, PT Bakrie & Brothers Tbk, and others, with significant share ownership and control. As of August 2024, the Bakrie family holds substantial stakes in these companies, with total shares valued at billions of rupiah, solidifying their influence in the Indonesian business landscape.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 0, "management": 2, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/50939/appointed-munaslub-kadin-list-companies-managed-anindya-bakrie", "sub_sector": ["media-entertainment"], "tags": ["Executive Changes", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["VIVA.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-09-18T14:59:38", "title": "Anindya Novyan Bakrie Appointed as General Chairperson of Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry Amidst Ties to Multiple Companies."}, {"body": "PT United Tractors (UNTR) plans to diversify its mining business, targeting a 34% year-on-year increase in gold sales volume to 235,000 ounces in 2024, and expanding into renewable energy, including mini-hydro, solar PV, and geothermal. Meanwhile, despite declining coal prices, UNTR aims to boost its operational performance in 2024, with a 12% year-on-year increase in coal production to 144 million tons and a 9% year-on-year increase in coal sales volume to 12.9 million tons.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 2, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "industrials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/50938/coal-business-expansion-untr-confident-branching-mineral-mining-nre", "sub_sector": ["industrial-goods"], "tags": ["Energy Commodities", "Gold", "Metals and Minerals", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["UNTR.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-09-18T14:46:01", "title": "PT United Tractors Shifts Focus from Coal Mining to Mineral Diversification and Renewable Energy"}]